@NODE Guide


    SplitGuide  GUIDE/A,DIR
    JoinGuide   SOURCE/A,GUIDE/A

These 2 commands were used in making the Gui4Cli guide.

Splitguide   - will split an AmigaGuide document into files, each node
               becoming a file with the same name as the node.
	GUIDE  - is the guide name
	DIR    - (optional) is the dir to place the resulting files.
		 if DIR is not declared, they will be placed in ram:

JoinGuide    - will join all the files in a directory into a complete
	       AmigaGuide document, also making an INDEX of the nodes.
	SOURCE - is the name of the DIR where the files (nodes) are
	GUIDE  - is the name of the resulting guide.

I made these because I find it a lot easier to work with small files
than with a huge 200k bugger..


