@NODE ILBMSize


   ILBMSize  ILBM_FILE

  A simple command which will print out the size & depth of an
  IFF-ILBM picture.

  The output will be something like :

  > 400 200 5

  meaning : width=400 pixels, height=200 pixels, depth=5 bitplanes

  You can get the number of colours by calculating 2 to the power
  of the number of bitplanes, i.e. in the above example, the
  picture has 2 to the 5th => (2*2*2*2*2) = 32 colours 

  May come useful in scripts..



